Why 30K?

30K is the first technology of its kind, and it was built from scratch. Because of that all our people are the top gurus of all-things frequent flyer. And you will too.

Our vision

We're a small team of young and passionate people. We don't respect rules, we respect values. We work remotely in an extremely mobile environment but still very closely. We put the focus on delivering, not on process.

Job description

We are looking for Data Integrity Analyst to help manage, control, and assure quality of the frequent flyer program data in our database.

The job involves a complete responsibility of the operational quality of the content of our product, which consists of the earning, redemption, and benefit rules of 70 frequent flyer programs. The position reports to the Programs Operations Manager based out of Manila.

Requirements
Bachelor’s/College Degree in Business, Finance, Economics, Accounting, Statistics, Mathematics or any equivalent or related course - Fresh graduates are encouraged to apply;
Knowledge and experience in using MS Office;
Good oral and written communication;
Strong attention to detail and analytical skills with ability to summarize/break down complex information into simpler terms/units of data;
Self-motivated, highly adaptable and results driven;
Ability to work in a team-oriented environment and under tight deadlines;
Experience in data collection, business research and customer service would be an advantage;
Must be willing to work in Makati.
Responsibilities
Managing database content and understanding how it impacts the product,
Identifying and adding missing content, information and programs,
Contacts with Frequent Flyer Programs and retrieval of information,
Organizing quality assurance methods,
Contribute in formulating database development and enhancement requirements as well as additional features and products with Head of Product.
Terms
Full time;
Competitive salary;
Flexible work schedule;
Opportunity to grow with the company;
Training and support provided.
How to apply?

Send us your resume and short message explaining why would you like to work with us to address: jobs@30k.com.

Job Duties

Organize and analyze data of the company’s business lines of global strategic logistic and other related or interested lines;

Research and analyze current market needs in transportation industry both in the U. S. and Asian countries, such as: China, Japan, Taiwan, and South East Asian market;

Research and study competitor’s business lines, services, and pricing;

Prepare periodical as well as timely research reports so as to provide advisory opinions for the company’s business policies and strategies formulation and adjustment;

Conduct regular and systematic market research with a focus on the changing market needs, prices, market developing tendencies, competitors’ marketing patterns, etc; and

Study and collect specific business policies, laws and codes and familiarize with relevant business procedures and practices in target countries and areas.




This position needs a Bachelor’s degree in Business Administration or a related field. Salary will be negotiated, based on experience and performance. CV to East-West Associates, Inc. 14821 Northam St., La Mirada, CA 90638.


